The paper deals with the computational complexity of computing equilibria in Arrow-Debreu exchange markets under various utility and production functions. This falls under the area of computational game theory (cs.GT) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also involves the reduction of multivariate polynomial equations to Leontief exchange markets, which could be classified under algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the paper discusses the complexity class ETR, which is related to real algebraic geometry and could be classified under computational complexity (cs.CC) and theoretical computer science (cs.THE).
